Over 50 worshippers were killed after gunmen attacked St. FrancisÂ Catholic Church in Owo, Ondo State, Nigeria, during the mass service on Sunday morning, the Nigerian Tribune reported. A source told the media outlet that gunmen had opened fire and used explosives within the church compound. The gunmen were said to have fled the scene immediately after they carried out the killing. Local police said they are investigating the cause of the shooting.